        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro drops as confidence in American economy eases concern that stock losses could lead foreign investors to pull money out; in New York, euro settles at 86.88 cents, down from 87.16 cents; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE EURO FALLS. The euro dropped as confidence in the American economy eased concern that stock losses could lead foreign investors to pull money out. In New York, the euro settled at 86.88 cents, down from 87.16 cents.</p>
      </block>
